00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,768
Yes, I saw that.

256
00:13:26,802 --> 00:13:30,438
And sometimes my family
can be unappreciative.

257
00:13:35,110 --> 00:13:37,979
But what happened today
can never happen again.

258
00:13:38,013 --> 00:13:39,947
I know.

259
00:13:40,772 --> 00:13:43,818
Listen, I grew up with
an alcoholic mother.

260
00:13:46,288 --> 00:13:50,057
I know what it like to
be angry all the time.

261
00:13:50,092 --> 00:13:54,996
But when I was your age,
I had to find a way...

262
00:13:57,166 --> 00:13:59,534
To control myself.

263
00:14:00,969 --> 00:14:02,904
How did you do that?

264
00:14:05,374 --> 00:14:06,808
A lot of help.

265
00:14:06,842 --> 00:14:09,243
One thing--I had a great
counselor at school,

266
00:14:09,278 --> 00:14:10,978
and she taught me

267
00:14:11,013 --> 00:14:14,081
that whenever I was
about to lose it,

268
00:14:14,116 --> 00:14:15,983
that I should do this...

269
00:14:18,008 --> 00:14:19,287
One.

270
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,522
Two.

271
00:14:22,185 --> 00:14:23,224
Three.

272
00:14:23,258 --> 00:14:25,359
That really works?

273
00:14:25,394 --> 00:14:27,461
It really does.

274
00:14:29,598 --> 00:14:31,499
It gives you a chance

275
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:33,601
to step back,

276
00:14:33,635 --> 00:14:36,103
feel like you're in control.

277
00:14:36,138 --> 00:14:38,673
You should try it next time.
You'll see.

278
00:14:40,231 --> 00:14:41,209
Okay.

279
00:14:44,379 --> 00:14:46,247
Mm.

280
00:14:48,784 --> 00:14:51,519
I'm really sorry about what I did.

281
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:54,037
It's fine.

282
00:14:54,038 --> 00:14:56,339
Just don't ever do it again.

283
00:15:01,135 --> 00:15:03,299
But thank you for wanting to.

284
00:15:12,623 --> 00:15:15,626
Oh, come on, Larry.You're my business
manager too.

285
00:15:15,627 --> 00:15:17,683
I am not leaving this
office until you tell me

286
00:15:17,684 --> 00:15:20,496
what Carlos is doing
with my ski house money.

287
00:15:20,531 --> 00:15:22,878
Gaby, you're putting me in
an uncomfortable position.

288
00:15:22,879 --> 00:15:24,457
You should talk to Carlos.

289
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:25,888
I did!

290
00:15:25,889 --> 00:15:28,320
I offered to put myself in a
very uncomfortable position,

291
00:15:28,321 --> 00:15:29,545
and he still said no.

292
00:15:29,546 --> 00:15:31,943
I'm sorry, but Carlos
swore me to secrecy.

293
00:15:31,944 --> 00:15:34,784
Please respect that.

294
00:15:34,978 --> 00:15:37,093
You're right. I'm sorry.

295
00:15:37,094 --> 00:15:38,247
No hard feelings.

296
00:15:38,282 --> 00:15:39,682
Of course not.

297
00:15:39,716 --> 00:15:41,306
Hey. What are you doing?

298
00:15:41,307 --> 00:15:43,760
Hmm. I don't want to be a liar.

299
00:15:43,761 --> 00:15:46,843
When I go home, and I'm in
tears and Carlos asks me why,

300
00:15:46,844 --> 00:15:48,961
and I say you grabbed my ass,

301
00:15:48,962 --> 00:15:51,394
I want to be telling the truth.

302
00:15:51,859 --> 00:15:54,397
Well played.

303
00:15:54,431 --> 00:15:57,467
Carlos gave $50,
000 to one of your neighbors.

304
00:15:57,501 --> 00:15:59,936
What?! Who?!

305
00:15:59,970 --> 00:16:03,072
A Mike Delfino. Apparently,
his business is in big trouble.

306
00:16:03,107 --> 00:16:06,008
Oh, my God. Mike's wife is one
of my closest friends,

307
00:16:06,043 --> 00:16:08,242
and she never said a word.

308
00:16:08,243 --> 00:16:09,498
Poor thing.

309
00:16:09,499 --> 00:16:12,181
Please don't tell
Carlos I told you.

310
00:16:12,216 --> 00:16:14,283
Of course.

311
00:16:14,318 --> 00:16:16,329
I should get going.

312
00:16:16,330 --> 00:16:17,788
Do you have parking validation?

313
00:16:17,789 --> 00:16:20,978
Oh, those are only for employees.

314
00:16:21,525 --> 00:16:23,659
Okay, you could take mine.

315
00:16:25,696 --> 00:16:28,830
Hotel, food, incidentals--

316
00:16:29,212 --> 00:16:30,388
$300.

317
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:32,426
You can order pay per view.

318
00:16:32,427 --> 00:16:33,585
I don't even care if you buy beer.

319
00:16:33,586 --> 00:16:36,007
Just stay in your room
as much as you can, okay?

320
00:16:36,008 --> 00:16:38,577
This is stupid. It's been 20 years.

321
00:16:38,611 --> 00:16:42,480
Have you actually seen or heard
from this Patrick Logan guy?

322
00:16:42,515 --> 00:16:44,781
Do you know for a fact
that he's even still alive?

323
00:16:44,782 --> 00:16:46,555
Danny, I'm not gonna
debate this with you.

324
00:16:46,556 --> 00:16:48,033
If he started this
group you guys were in,

325
00:16:48,034 --> 00:16:49,205
then isn't he on the run, too?

326
00:16:49,206 --> 00:16:52,015
He's got bigger problems
than getting revenge.

327
00:16:52,016 --> 00:16:53,370
Just humor me, okay?

328
00:16:53,371 --> 00:16:55,772
Because if I'm wrong,
all I am is wrong.

329
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,741
But if I'm not...

330
00:17:00,693 --> 00:17:03,480
Please. Just humor me.

331
00:17:10,621 --> 00:17:12,520
Check stand one is now open.

332
00:17:12,521 --> 00:17:13,630
Hello.

333
00:17:13,631 --> 00:17:16,024
Check stand one is now open,
taking all customers...

334
00:17:16,025 --> 00:17:17,493
Hello.

335
00:17:17,528 --> 00:17:19,562
Um, I saw you the other day,

336
00:17:19,597 --> 00:17:22,432
talking to my friend Sam.

337
00:17:22,466 --> 00:17:24,968
Oh, I'm--I'm Bree, by the way.

338
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:26,936
I know who you are.

339
00:17:29,807 --> 00:17:32,041
Well, this is none of my business,

340
00:17:32,076 --> 00:17:37,714
but I noticed that there was
some tension between you two.

341
00:17:37,748 --> 00:17:39,649
You could say that.

342
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:43,720
Oh. Well, I hope
everything is okay.

343
00:17:44,822 --> 00:17:46,856
What is it you want?

344
00:17:49,093 --> 00:17:50,233
Well, I don't know.

345
00:17:50,234 --> 00:17:54,964
There was just something so
odd about that... encounter.

346
00:17:54,999 --> 00:17:58,668
I don't understand why he would
talk to a friend like that.

347
00:18:02,139 --> 00:18:05,074
Maybe that's because
I'm not his friend.

348
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,444
I'm his mother.

349
00:18:17,186 --> 00:18:20,654
My manager said I could
take a break early.

350
00:18:20,655 --> 00:18:22,623
You've got five minutes.

351
00:18:23,418 --> 00:18:27,293
Are you aware that Sam goes around
telling people that you're--

352
00:18:27,294 --> 00:18:28,810
dead.

353
00:18:30,165 --> 00:18:31,432
Yes, I heard.

354
00:18:31,433 --> 00:18:33,514
Why would he do that?

355
00:18:36,038 --> 00:18:38,206
He's a complicated boy.

356
00:18:43,045 --> 00:18:46,347
Did Sam tell you
who his father was?

357
00:18:46,381 --> 00:18:49,951
He told me about your
relationship with my... husband,

358
00:18:49,985 --> 00:18:53,087
if that's what you're referring to.

359
00:18:53,839 --> 00:18:57,258
Did he also mention the
letter that Rex sent to me?

360
00:18:57,292 --> 00:18:59,127
What letter?

361
00:18:59,161 --> 00:19:01,062
It was after you were married.

362
00:19:01,096 --> 00:19:02,997
Rex had just started his practice,

363
00:19:03,031 --> 00:19:06,667
and apparently,
the money was pouring in.

364
00:19:08,203 --> 00:19:09,835
Rex wrote

365
00:19:09,836 --> 00:19:14,441
and told me he could
give Sam a better life.

366
00:19:14,442 --> 00:19:17,252
He then asked for
full-time custody.

367
00:19:20,505 --> 00:19:23,127
I'm guessing he
never told you that.

368
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:26,520
Must have slipped his mind.

369
00:19:26,521 --> 00:19:30,137
I politely declined his offer.

370
00:19:30,138 --> 00:19:33,729
And did Sam... know about this?

371
00:19:34,347 --> 00:19:35,397
Not until a few months ago,

372
00:19:35,398 --> 00:19:38,132
when he found the letter.

373
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:41,969
And when he realized that he
could have lived all those years

374
00:19:42,004 --> 00:19:46,073
with his dad in a fancy house...

375
00:19:46,108 --> 00:19:50,011
He... was beyond livid.

376
00:19:50,045 --> 00:19:54,882
Even so, how could he go around
pretending that you're dead?

377
00:19:56,852 --> 00:19:59,487
Like I said...

378
00:19:59,521 --> 00:20:01,789
He's a complicated boy.

379
00:20:08,730 --> 00:20:10,131
Gaby, hi.

380
00:20:10,165 --> 00:20:12,533
Hi, Susan.

381
00:20:12,568 --> 00:20:14,468
I just got back
from the supermarket

382
00:20:14,503 --> 00:20:16,778
and realized I bought way too much.

383
00:20:16,779 --> 00:20:18,283
I'm afraid some of
it's gonna go bad,

384
00:20:18,284 --> 00:20:19,985
and so I thought,
who could I give this to?

385
00:20:19,986 --> 00:20:23,268
And I randomly thought of you.

386
00:20:25,424 --> 00:20:27,355
You're afraid that canned peaches

387
00:20:27,356 --> 00:20:29,659
and condensed milk
are going to go bad?

388
00:20:29,818 --> 00:20:33,257
Well, it's just,
my cupboards are cluttered,

389
00:20:33,258 --> 00:20:36,190
and you'd be doing me a huge favor.

390
00:20:36,225 --> 00:20:37,658
Okay.

391
00:20:37,693 --> 00:20:38,659
Thanks.

392
00:20:38,694 --> 00:20:40,494
Oh. Hey.

393
00:20:40,529 --> 00:20:42,563
As long as you're here,

394
00:20:42,598 --> 00:20:44,699
I want to show you something.

395
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:50,104
Wow.

396
00:20:50,138 --> 00:20:51,873
We just got it.

397
00:20:51,907 --> 00:20:54,542
M.J. Is gonna take lessons.

398
00:20:55,811 --> 00:20:58,246
You sure you don't
want to start him off

399
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,581
with, say, a used upright?

400
00:21:00,616 --> 00:21:02,083
No way.

401
00:21:02,117 --> 00:21:05,386
Me wan-NY, me like-y, me get-Ty.

402
00:21:07,189 --> 00:21:11,425
May I ask how much this cost-y?

403
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:15,596
Well, Mike doesn't like me
throwing around numbers,

404
00:21:15,631 --> 00:21:19,500
but let's just say
your jaw would drop...

405
00:21:19,534 --> 00:21:21,602
30,000 times.

406
00:21:22,434 --> 00:21:23,169
Wha--

407
00:21:23,170 --> 00:21:25,439
that's one.

408
00:21:25,474 --> 00:21:27,708
This is none of my business,

409
00:21:27,743 --> 00:21:30,645
but is this really the best time

410
00:21:30,679 --> 00:21:32,713
to buy something this expensive?

411
00:21:32,748 --> 00:21:36,017
I mean, didn't Mike just
have his truck repossessed?

412
00:21:36,863 --> 00:21:39,287
Things finally turned around.

413
00:21:39,321 --> 00:21:41,489
He got a big cash infusion.

414
00:21:41,523 --> 00:21:43,524
You don't say.

415
00:21:43,558 --> 00:21:47,261
Anyway, I know you guys
don't have a piano,

416
00:21:47,296 --> 00:21:50,531
so if you ever want the
girls to take lessons...

417
00:21:52,401 --> 00:21:54,402
Well, thank you. I gotta go.

418
00:21:54,436 --> 00:21:55,903
Enjoy your peaches.

419
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:05,146
You owe me $50,000.

420
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:07,048
What? For your information,

421
00:22:07,082 --> 00:22:10,584
Mike's "big cash infusion"
cost me my ski house.

422
00:22:10,619 --> 00:22:12,552
What are you talking about?

423
00:22:12,553 --> 00:22:13,748
Oh, don't play dumb.

424
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:16,924
Carlos loaned Mike the 50 grand,
and you know it!

425
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,895
Why are you looking
like you don't know it?

426
00:22:22,056 --> 00:22:23,731
He told me...

427
00:22:23,765 --> 00:22:25,298
Business picked up.

428
00:22:25,299 --> 00:22:26,164
Well, he lied,

429
00:22:26,165 --> 00:22:28,862
just like Carlos lied to me
about where our money went,

430
00:22:28,863 --> 00:22:31,472
which you went and
spent on a piano.

431
00:22:31,506 --> 00:22:34,308
Oh, no--no, I didn't. Uh...

432
00:22:35,777 --> 00:22:37,912
I inherited it.

433
00:22:37,946 --> 00:22:40,014
I was trying to make you jealous.

434
00:22:40,874 --> 00:22:42,015
Oh, honey,

435
00:22:42,016 --> 00:22:45,653
given different circumstances,
that so would have worked.

436
00:22:47,923 --> 00:22:50,324
This is unbelievable.

437
00:22:50,359 --> 00:22:52,927
I have the money
from the strip club

438
00:22:52,961 --> 00:22:54,462
sitting in the bank,

439
00:22:54,496 --> 00:22:57,765
and Mike would rather
borrow it from you guys?

440
00:23:00,202 --> 00:23:02,236
I'm about to screech at my husband.

441
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:04,171
You might want to stand back.

442
00:23:04,496 --> 00:23:06,107
No, no, no, no, no.

443
00:23:06,141 --> 00:23:08,516
I have a better idea.

444
00:23:10,316 --> 00:23:11,545
There you are.

445
00:23:11,546 --> 00:23:13,183
Hey.

446
00:23:13,415 --> 00:23:15,916
Hey, Mr. Scavo. How was the flight?

447
00:23:15,951 --> 00:23:18,085
Horrible. It was delayed,

448
00:23:18,086 --> 00:23:19,552
there was turbulence,

449
00:23:19,553 --> 00:23:21,589
they ran out of food,

450
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:25,717
and I'm not seeing a plate
covered with tinfoil here.

451
00:23:25,718 --> 00:23:28,715
There was one, but one of our 50
children must have inhaled it.

452
00:23:28,716 --> 00:23:30,431
Damn it!

453
00:23:30,465 --> 00:23:31,932
Okay, calm down.

454
00:23:31,933 --> 00:23:34,702
Lynette, no. I'm hungry.
You know, when you were working,

455
00:23:34,736 --> 00:23:36,400
I always had food waiting for you.

456
00:23:36,401 --> 00:23:37,307
Oh, that's right.

457
00:23:37,308 --> 00:23:39,541
You were very considerate
in your eighth month.

458
00:23:39,542 --> 00:23:40,674
I'm sorry. I keep forgetting,

459
00:23:40,709 --> 00:23:42,691
you're the only person who's
ever been pregnant before.

460
00:23:42,692 --> 00:23:46,113
Relax. Relax.
We'll just order a pizza.

461
00:23:46,148 --> 00:23:49,083
And wait an hour? Forget it.
I'll fend for myself.

462
00:23:49,084 --> 00:23:50,878
Six, seven,

463
00:23:50,879 --> 00:23:53,054
eight, nine...

464
00:23:53,088 --> 00:23:55,856
Hey, it's okay. I'm fine.

465
00:23:55,891 --> 00:23:58,292
There's nothing in here.

466
00:23:58,326 --> 00:24:01,180
Come on. Lynette, you didn't go
to the store today? 16... 17...

467
00:24:01,181 --> 00:24:03,031
Sweetie, you might want
to take it down a notch.

468
00:24:03,032 --> 00:24:04,726
I have been in three
cities in two days.

469
00:24:04,727 --> 00:24:08,725
You'd think you'd find the time
to go to the market. 21, 22...

470
00:24:08,726 --> 00:24:10,309
What the hell is he doing?

471
00:24:10,310 --> 00:24:12,044
Eddie, it's okay.

472
00:24:12,078 --> 00:24:14,279
23, 24, 25... tell him
to stick a sock in it.

473
00:24:14,314 --> 00:24:15,748
26, 27...

474
00:24:15,782 --> 00:24:18,691
Okay, you need to kiss me.
Here. Mmm!

475
00:24:18,692 --> 00:24:20,719
Okay, there. We're good.
We're good. He loves me.

476
00:24:20,754 --> 00:24:23,555
He loves me.

477
00:24:29,289 --> 00:24:31,063
We'll talk about it later.

478
00:24:36,090 --> 00:24:38,358
So Eddie attacked our son?

479
00:24:38,392 --> 00:24:40,432
Okay, I'd use "attack,
" but with a small "a."

480
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:44,264
Okay, that's it. I want him out,
and that's with a big "o."

481
00:24:44,298 --> 00:24:47,467
Look, Eddie is not some
exchange student from France.

482
00:24:47,502 --> 00:24:49,402
He comes from an abusive home.

483
00:24:49,437 --> 00:24:53,173
We have to accept he
has some... baggage.

484
00:24:53,207 --> 00:24:55,786
So I have to wonder
if he's gonna punch me

485
00:24:55,787 --> 00:24:58,543
any time I raise my voice to you?

486
00:24:58,544 --> 00:25:01,744
I am not sending him back to
live with that woman, Tom.

487
00:25:03,551 --> 00:25:05,919
How about therapy? That might help.

488
00:25:05,953 --> 00:25:07,888
Now we're gonna pay
for his therapy?

489
00:25:07,922 --> 00:25:10,597
Okay, here's a thought.
How about we all stop yelling at me?

490
00:25:10,598 --> 00:25:13,634
What a concept-
be nice to Lynette.

491
00:25:14,188 --> 00:25:15,316
Fine.

492
00:25:15,317 --> 00:25:17,398
We'll try the therapy.

493
00:25:18,166 --> 00:25:20,133
All these weeks,
Sam has been going on

494
00:25:20,134 --> 00:25:22,369
about how his mother was dead,
and the whole time,

495
00:25:22,370 --> 00:25:26,806
she has been at Howe's market,
in a smock, stacking cans.

496
00:25:26,998 --> 00:25:30,510
I guess my instincts about Sam
were right, wouldn't you say?

497
00:25:30,545 --> 00:25:32,646
What did I say about gloating?

498
00:25:32,896 --> 00:25:34,915
Something. I wasn't listening.

499
00:25:34,949 --> 00:25:37,749
I was thinking about
how right I was.

500
00:25:38,796 --> 00:25:40,819
Okay, I'll stop.
I know you're upset.

501
00:25:40,820 --> 00:25:42,351
You have no idea.

502
00:25:42,352 --> 00:25:43,487
When Sam first showed up,

503
00:25:43,488 --> 00:25:46,343
I felt like I got a
little piece of Rex back.

504
00:25:46,344 --> 00:25:48,844
It was wonderful.

505
00:25:48,845 --> 00:25:50,320
But this has forced me to remember

506
00:25:50,321 --> 00:25:53,233
that Rex was a liar, too.

507
00:26:01,442 --> 00:26:04,010
Sorry. Am I interrupting something?

508
00:26:06,647 --> 00:26:08,548
Orson, would you please excuse us?

509
00:26:08,583 --> 00:26:10,150
Of course.

510
00:26:14,555 --> 00:26:16,289
Everything all right?

511
00:26:16,324 --> 00:26:17,791
Actually, Sam--

512
00:26:17,825 --> 00:26:20,126
wait, wait. Still here.

513
00:26:22,997 --> 00:26:25,632
I went back to the
supermarket today.

514
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,674
I take it you met my mother.

515
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,096
Why did you say she was dead?

516
00:26:38,097 --> 00:26:40,945
She is dead... to me.

517
00:26:40,946 --> 00:26:43,946
