766
00:40:19,519 --> 00:40:22,296
Aren't you afraid I'll
kill you in your sleep?

767
00:40:22,297 --> 00:40:23,824
Angie,

768
00:40:23,825 --> 00:40:26,776
if the last 20 years
have taught us anything,

769
00:40:26,777 --> 00:40:29,447
it's that you're not
comfortable killing people.

770
00:40:33,377 --> 00:40:36,520
And if you decide to run away,
just make sure

771
00:40:36,521 --> 00:40:38,649
you stop by the hospital
and say good-bye to Nick,

772
00:40:38,650 --> 00:40:41,785
because he won't be around
much longer after you've gone.

773
00:40:41,786 --> 00:40:44,015
Patrick, please, don't hurt him.

774
00:40:44,016 --> 00:40:48,230
Just do what I tell you, baby,
and I'll let you both live.

775
00:40:48,231 --> 00:40:52,569
<i>Mysterious men--</i>

776
00:40:53,724 --> 00:40:58,369
<i>they make promises they have
no intention of keeping.</i>

777
00:41:01,300 --> 00:41:04,911
<i>They tell lies to get
what they want.</i>

778
00:41:07,905 --> 00:41:11,981
<i>They may be more dangerous
than they seem.</i>

779
00:41:13,237 --> 00:41:17,444
<i>Yes, our mothers told us</i>

780
00:41:17,445 --> 00:41:21,106
<i>we cannot trust the men
we don't know.</i>

781
00:41:22,701 --> 00:41:25,132
<i>And those we do know?</i>

782
00:41:26,255 --> 00:41:30,538
<i>Well, we can't always
trust them either.</i>

